| Concept 		| What it does 					| When to use it				|
|---------		|-------------					|---------------				|
| `socket()` 	| Creates a socket fd 			| Once at startup 				|
| `bind()` 		| Attaches socket to a port		| Once at startup 				|
| `listen()` 	| Starts accepting connections 	| Once at startup 				|
| `accept()` 	| Gets a new client connection 	| When `server_fd` has POLLIN 	|
| `poll()` 		| Monitors multiple fds			| Every loop iteration 			|
| `read()` 		| Reads data from client		| When `client_fd` has POLLIN 	|
| `write()` 	| Sends data to client			| After processing message 		|
| `close()` 	| Closes connection				| When client disconnects		|


htons()
===================
 ==>	PC dyalk kaykhdem b little endian

 ==>	network kaykhdem b big endian
